      <node id="MORRISH SC, 2011, J RES MARK ENTREP" label="MORRISH SC, 2011, J RES MARK ENTREP">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING: A STRATEGY FOR THE TWENTY-FIRST CENTURY?" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="MORRISH SC" />
          <attvalue for="3" value="SUSSIE MORRISH" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2900-3232" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="PURPOSE - THE PURPOSE OF THIS PAPER IS TO PRESENT THE AUTHOR'S VIEW OF THE ROLE OF ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING (EM) AS A STRATEGY TO ADDRESS THE DYNAMIC MARKETING ENVIRONMENT OF RECENT TIMES. DESIGN/METHODOLOGY/APPROACH - THE AUTHOR REFLECTS ON SOME SIGNIFICANT MARKETING CHANGES AND PROVIDES SOME CONTEMPORARY EXAMPLE OF COMPANIES THAT HAVE SUCCESSFULLY ADOPTED EM APPROACHES AND CHALLENGED TRADITIONAL MARKETING WISDOM. FINDINGS - EM IS BEST CONCEIVED NOT AS A NEXUS BETWEEN MARKETING AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP, BUT AS AN AUGMENTED PROCESS, WHERE BOTH THE ENTREPRENEUR AND THE CUSTOMER ARE THE CORE ACTORS, CO-CREATING VALUE WITHIN THE MARKETING ENVIRONMENT. ORIGINALITY/VALUE - WHILE THIS IS AN OPINION PIECE, THE PAPER PROVIDES EVIDENCE OF HOW EM CAN BE ADOPTED AND APPLIED BY ENTREPRENEURIAL FIRMS AND CHALLENGES MARKETERS TO CREATE AND CONTROL THEIR OWN-MARKETING ENVIRONMENT." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2011.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="JOURNAL OF RESEARCH IN MARKETING AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="J RES MARK ENTREP" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="NEW ZEALAND" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.1108/14715201111176390" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.1108/14715201111176390" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
