          <attvalue for="1" value="THE EFFECT OF MARKET ORIENTATION TOWARDS SMALL AND MEDIUM ENTERPRISES BATIK ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING: A CASE STUDY IN INDONESIA" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="NUVRIASARI A;SUYANTO M;AZMAN MNA" />
          <attvalue for="3" value="AUDITA NUVRIASARI; MOHAMMAD SUYANTO; MOHAMED YUSOFF MOHD NOR; AZHARI AZMAN; A SHEHU; F BOACHIE-MENSAH; K ISSAU; M AMIN; THURASAMY; A ALDAKHIL; A KASWURI; I SUARDHIKA; N SURYANI; P KILENTHONG; C HULTMAN; G HILLS; D IONITA; M MORRIS; M SCHINDEHUTTE; R LAFORGE; R JONES; M SUORANTA; J ROWLEY; S KRAUS; R HARMS; M FINK; L NIEHM; J HURST; J SON; A FIORE; A SADACHAR; R BECHERER; M HELMS; J MCDONALD; G HACIOGLU; S EREN; M EREN; H CELIKKAN; I NWAIZUGBO; A ANUKAM; S MORRISH; M MILES; J DEACON; A HOQUE; Z AWAN; U GWADABE; A NUVRIASARI; A ISHAK; A HIDAYAT; Z MUSTAFA; S HARYONO; A KALSOM; H AB RAHIM; R BECHERER; M HELMS; D PUSPITA; M MUCHLAS; T KUAT; J NARVER; S SLATER; R HURLEY; G HULT; P KILENTHONG; C HULTMAN; G HILLS; J NARVER; S SLATER; D MACLACHLAN; S HA; M LO; T RAMAYAH; T LEE; H TSAI; K TAJEDDINI; M TRUEMAN; G LARSEN; W ALHAKIMI; M MAHMOUD; J ZHANG; Y DUAN; J HAN; N KIM; R SRIVASTAVA; S LIU; A RISWANTO; R RASTO; H HENDRAYATI; M SAPARUDIN; A ABIDIN; A EKA; M TOGHRAEE; M REZVANI; M MOBARAKI; J FARSI; S HUNT; R MORGAN; S LONIAL; R CARTER; A KOHLI; B JAWORSKI; W BAKER; J SINKULA; A LEAL RODRGUEZ; G ALBORT-MORANT; G LUMPKIN; G DESS; G HULT; R HURLEY; G KNIGHT; C LIN; C PENG; D KAO; H GULE; M ZERENLER; V CAGLIYAN; T SENER; K KARABOGA; P WHALEN; M AKAKA; A FIORE; L NIEHM; J HURST; J SON; A SADACHAR; S MORRISH; B LUKAS; O FERRELL; A NEWMAN; D PRAJOGO; A ATHERTON; S IM; J WORKMAN; K ZHOU; J BROWN; C DEV; M O'DWYER; A GILMORE; M WESTERLUND; S LEMINEN; J LU; G ZHANG; M HABIBZADEH; F ALIZADEH MESHKANI; A HAJIPOOR SHOSHTARI; E AL-MANASRA; M AL-ZYADAT; M AL-AWAMREH; M ALNSOUR" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="NO ORCID; https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5893-7600; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID; NO ORCID" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="MARKETING IS AN ESSENTIAL KEY FOR SMES TO GROW AND SURVIVE. THEREFORE, ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING (EM) AS A MARKETING PRACTICE SUITABLE FOR SMALL FIRMS NEEDS TO BE ANALYZED. THIS STUDY CONTRIBUTES TO EM KNOWLEDGE BY PROPOSING MARKET ORIENTATION THAT CONSIST OF CUSTOMER ORIENTATION, COMPETITOR ORIENTATION, AND INTERFUNCTIONAL COORDINATION AS ANTECEDENTS OF EM AND INNOVATIVENESS AS A MEDIATOR. 260 BATIK SMES LOCATED IN THE SPECIAL REGION OF YOGYAKARTA, INDONESIA WERE SELECTED AS THE SAMPLES OF THIS STUDY. THE RESULTS CONCLUDE THAT INTERFUNCTIONAL COORDINATION HAS A SIGNIFICANT POSITIVE EFFECT ON EM. MEANWHILE, CUSTOMER AND COMPETITOR ORIENTATION HAD NO SIGNIFICANT EFFECT ON EM. THESE FINDINGS ALSO PROVIDE NEW INSIGHTS INTO THE ROLE OF INNOVATIVENESS AS A MEDIATOR BETWEEN INTERFUNCTIONAL COORDINATION AND EM." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2022.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="QUALITY-ACCESS TO SUCCESS" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="QUAL-ACCESS SUCCESS" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="INDONESIA; INDONESIA; MALAYSIA" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.47750/QAS/23.188.16" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.47750/qas/23.188.16" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
      <node id="SARMA M, 2022, SUSTAINABILITY-BASEL" label="SARMA M, 2022, SUSTAINABILITY-BASEL">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="THE ROLE OF ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING IN THE INDONESIAN AGRO-BASED INDUSTRY CLUSTER TO FACE THE ASEAN ECONOMIC COMMUNITY" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="SARMA M;SEPTIANI S;NANERE M" />
          <attvalue for="3" value="SARMA, MA'MUN;SEPTIANI, STEVIA;NANERE, MARTHIN" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="SARMA, MAMUN/0000-0003-3356-7866; SEPTIANI, STEVIA/0000-0003-0595-0358" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="THE AGRO-INDUSTRY PLAYS AN IMPORTANT ROLE IN THE INDONESIAN ECONOMY. HOWEVER, MICRO, SMALL AND MEDIUM ENTERPRISES (MSMES) IN THIS INDUSTRY FACE VARIOUS CHALLENGES TO BE COMPETITIVE, ONE OF WHICH IS THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE ASEAN ECONOMIC COMMUNITY (AEC) AGREEMENT. THE STUDY AIMS TO DEVELOP A MODEL FOR THE AGRO-INDUSTRY MICRO-SMALL MEDIUM ENTERPRISES TO FACE THE ASEAN ECONOMIC COMMUNITY (AEC) USING ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING APPROACHES. THIS RESEARCH WAS CONDUCTED AT THREE CENTERS OF AGRO-BASED INDUSTRY CLUSTERS IN INDONESIA. THE RESPONDENTS WERE BUSINESS ACTORS REPRESENTING THE LEADING MICRO-SMALL AND MEDIUM ENTERPRISES (MSMES) IN THE FRUIT-PROCESSING INDUSTRY CLUSTER, FISH PROCESSING INDUSTRY CLUSTER AND MILK PROCESSING INDUSTRY CLUSTER. PRIMARY DATA COLLECTION WAS CONDUCTED THROUGH STRUCTURED INTERVIEWS USING CLOSE ENDED QUESTIONNAIRES. THIS STUDY USED STRUCTURAL EQUATION MODELLING ANALYSIS WITH A PARTIAL LEAST SQUARES (PLS) APPROACH TO DEVELOP A MODEL OF ENHANCEMENT FOR THE AGRO-INDUSTRY CLUSTERS IN DEALING WITH AEC. THE FINDINGS SUGGEST THAT THE ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING HAS SIGNIFICANT IMPACT IN INCREASING BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT AND BUSINESS COMPETITIVENESS. THE MSMES POSSESSING GREAT COMPETITIVENESS WOULD BE MORE READY TO PENETRATE THEIR BUSINESS INTO OTHER ASEAN MARKETS. IN ADDITION, SUPPORTIVE GOVERNMENT POLICIES THAT ENCOURAGE AND IMPROVE INNOVATIVENESS CAN SIGNIFICANTLY INCREASE THE ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING ABILITY." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2022.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="SUSTAINABILITY" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="SUSTAINABILITY-BASEL" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="INDONESIA; AUSTRALIA" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.3390/su14106163" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.3390/su14106163" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
