      <node id="HUNT S, 1997, J MARKETING" label="HUNT S, 1997, J MARKETING">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="RESOURCE-ADVANTAGE THEORY: A SNAKE SWALLOWING ITS TAIL OR A GENERAL THEORY OF COMPETITION?" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="HUNT S.D.; MORGAN R.M." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="SHELBY D. HUNT; ROBERT M. MORGAN" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="HTTPS://ORCID.ORG/0000-0002-8928-3400; " />
          <attvalue for="5" value="DELIGÖNÜL AND ÇAVUŞGIL (1997) CONDUCT A PARADIGM-LEVEL ANALYSIS OF RESOURCE-ADVANTAGE (R-A) THEORY. THEY ARGUE THAT (1) HUNT AND MORGAN (1995) OFFER RESOURCE-ADVANTAGE THEORY AS A REPLACEMENT FOR PERFECT COMPETITION THEORY, (2) A SUCCESSFUL CHALLENGER TO ANY THEORY MUST COME FROM A NEW PARADIGM, (3) BUT BOTH PERFECT COMPETITION AND R-A THEORY COME FROM THE SAME PARADIGM. THEREFORE, (4) THE REPLACEMENT THESIS IS DUBIOUS. WE EVALUATE THEIR ARGUMENT." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="1997.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="JOURNAL OF MARKETING" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="J MARKETING" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.1177/002224299706100406" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.1177/002224299706100406" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
