        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING: ANALYZING THE EFFECTS OF SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING ON BUSINESS ENTERPRISE PERFORMANCE" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="BOOPATHI M.; SHARMA N.; RAJ R.; PATIL P.S.; DHAMIJA A." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="MYTHILI BOOPATHI; NIHARIKA SHARMA; ROOP RAJ; PRASHANT PATIL; ARUNA DHAMIJA" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="THE MOST IMPORTANT BREAKTHROUGHS FOR THE COMPANY OVER THE LAST DECADES ARE ONLINE BUSINESS MARKETING. IN SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING, DUE TO ITS INTRICACY AND MULTIDIMENSIONALITY, TRUST HAS HISTORICALLY BEEN A PHRASE THAT HAS BEEN CHALLENGING TO QUANTIFY AND DEFINE. DESPITE THE INCREASING GROWTH OF COMMERCIAL WEBSITES, MANY CONSUMERS THINK THAT DOING BUSINESS ONLINE IS RISKIER THAN DOING IT OFFLINE. ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING IS AN ADVERTISING TACTICS THAT OFFER ENTREPRENEURS A MEANS TO EFFICIENTLY MANAGE THEIR FIRMS ON A TIGHT BUDGET. BECAUSE OF SOCIAL MEDIA, BUSINESSES NOW OPERATE VERY DIFFERENTLY. THIS RESEARCH EXPLORES THE SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING STRATEGIES INFLUENCING BUSINESS ENTERPRISES PERFORMANCE. THE MARKETING STRATEGIES OF ENTREPRENEURS WERE STUDIED USING THE CRITERIA SUCH AS CUSTOMER FOCUS, INNOVATIVENESS, PROACTIVE APPROACH AND VALUE CREATION. IN ADDITION, THERE ARE TWO ESSENTIAL PORTIONS IN THIS STUDY PAPER. THE FIRST SECTION IS DATA COLLECTION, WHICH INCLUDES A PRIMARY DATA SOURCE. THE INFORMATION OF THE STUDY WAS OBTAINED FROM UTTAR PRADESHS BUSINESS OWNERS BY EMPLOYING A STANDARDISED QUESTIONNAIRE. TO OBTAIN THE DESIRED FINDINGS, SEM ANALYSIS WAS CONDUCTED USING DATA ACQUIRED FROM THE RELEVANT AUTHORITIES.  2025 INFORMA UK LIMITED, TRADING AS TAYLOR &amp; FRANCIS GROUP." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2025.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="JOURNAL OF MARKETING COMMUNICATIONS" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="INDIA; INDIA; INDIA; INDIA; INDIA" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.1080/13527266.2025.2590533" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.1080/13527266.2025.2590533" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
