      <node id="JONES R, 2009" label="JONES R, 2009">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING IN SMALL WELSH TECHNOLOGY FIRMS : AN EMPIRICAL STUDY" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="JONES R." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="ROSALIND JONES" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="HTTPS://ORCID.ORG/0000-0003-2381-0519" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="THIS STUDY INVESTIGATES THE MARKETING OF SOFTWARE PRODUCTS AND SERVICES IN MICRO AND&amp;#13;\NSMALL FIRMS. THE NATURE OF THE SOFTWARE PRODUCT MEANS THAT IT IS THAT IT IS AN&amp;#13;\N'INTANGIBLE' PRODUCT. FIRMS IN THIS STUDY OFFER BOTH A PRODUCT AND A SERVICE SOFTWARE&amp;#13;\NSOLUTION WHICH OFTEN INCORPORATES PROJECT MANAGEMENT, CONSULTATION AND AFTER SALES&amp;#13;\NSUPPORT. THE NATURE OF THE RESEARCH PROBLEM THEREFORE REQUIRES A REVIEW OF A NUMBER&amp;#13;\NOF DISCIPLINES INCLUDING ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING (EM) AND SME MARKETING. THESE&amp;#13;\NCONCEPTS ARE ESPECIALLY PERTINENT TO SMALL FIRMS OPERATING IN HIGHLY COMPETITIVE AND&amp;#13;\NINNOVATIVE MARKETS AS THEY ATTEMPT TO BUILD MARKET SHARE BY DELIVERING A HIGH QUALITY&amp;#13;\NSERVICE WITH INNOVATIVE SOLUTIONS.&amp;#13;\NTHE RESEARCH APPROACH EMPLOYS AN INTEGRATIVE MULTIPLE MIX OF QUALITATIVE&amp;#13;\NMETHODOLOGIES. THIS METHOD INCLUDES AN EXTENDED CASE STUDY OF A MICRO SIZED&amp;#13;\NSOFTWARE TECHNOLOGY FIRM AND A SURVEY OF THE UK EDUCATIONAL SOFTWARE SECTOR IN&amp;#13;\NWHICH IT OPERATES. THE STUDY ALSO INCLUDES EXPLORATION OF OWNER-MANAGER NETWORKS&amp;#13;\NAND THE CUSTOMER'S VIEW OF THE IT PURCHASE DECISION. AN EMPIRICALLY AND&amp;#13;\NTHEORETICALLY DEVELOPED 'EMICO' FRAMEWORK WHICH LIES AT THE HEART OF THIS THESIS AND&amp;#13;\NIS USED FOR INVESTIGATION OF EM ACTIVITIES AND BEHAVIOURS IN SMALL SOFTWARE&amp;#13;\NTECHNOLOGY FIRMS. THIS MODEL IS TESTED AND CONSOLIDATED USING A PURPOSIVE SAMPLE OF&amp;#13;\NSIX MICRO AND SMALL SOFTWARE TECHNOLOGY FIRMS BASED IN NORTH WALES.&amp;#13;\NTHE FINDINGS REVEAL THAT THESE FIRMS ARE HIGHLY CUSTOMER AND INNOVATION ORIENTED IN&amp;#13;\NNATURE. KEY ISSUES FOR SMALL FIRMS IN THIS SECTOR INCLUDE: THE IMPORTANCE OF PROJECT&amp;#13;\NPLANNING, THE USE OF IT KNOWLEDGE INFRASTRUCTURES, BUILDING LONG TERM CUSTOMER&amp;#13;\NRELATIONSHIPS, MANAGING CUSTOMER EXPECTATIONS AND, USE OF NETWORKS. OWNERMANAGERS&amp;#13;\NMADE USE OF A RANGE OF NETWORKS WHILST FIRMS USED WORD OF MOUTH (WOM)&amp;#13;\NRECOMMENDATION,T ENDING TO BE RISK AVERSEA ND LOW IN COMPETITOR AWARENESSB UT&amp;#13;\NUSING WEB BASED TECHNOLOGY NETWORKS TO GLEAN INFORMATION ABOUT NEW INNOVATIONS&amp;#13;\NAND CHANGES IN THE MARKETPLACE.&amp;#13;\NTHIS THESIS MAKES A SIGNIFICANT CONTRIBUTION TO THE EM LITERATURE IN FIRST DEVELOPING&amp;#13;\NAND THEN REFINING THE 'EMICO' FRAMEWORK, A NEW QUALITATIVE RESEARCH FRAMEWORK&amp;#13;\NWITH WHICH TO INVESTIGATE ENTREPRENEURIAL MARKETING ACTIVITIES AND BEHAVIOURS IN&amp;#13;\NSMES. UP UNTIL NOW THERE HAS BEEN VERY LITTLE RESEARCH FOCUSSED ON THE SOFTWARE&amp;#13;\NTECHNOLOGY SECTOR WITH SPECIFIC REFERENCE TO SMES, AND SO THIS THESIS ALSO EXTENDS&amp;#13;\NKNOWLEDGE AND CONTRIBUTES TO THE LITERATURE IN THE AREA." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2009.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
      <node id="SHAW E, 1999" label="SHAW E, 1999">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="A GUIDE TO THE QUALITATIVE RESEARCH PROCESS: EVIDENCE FROM A SMALL FIRM STUDY" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="SHAW E." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="ELEANOR SHAW" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="HTTPS://ORCID.ORG/0000-0002-6614-6729" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="PROVIDES A DETAILED DESCRIPTION OF THE QUALITATIVE RESEARCH PROCESS EXPERIENCED BY THE AUTHOR WHEN UNDERTAKING DOCTORAL RESEARCH. RECOGNISING THAT THERE ARE FEW ARTICLES TO GUIDE THE QUALITATIVE SMALL FIRM RESEARCHER, IT IS THE INTENTION TO PROVIDE A DETAILED ACCOUNT OF THE PROCESS AND DECISIONS INVOLVED WHEN UNDERTAKING QUALITATIVE SMALL FIRM RESEARCH. FROM A DISCUSSION OF THE FACTORS THAT CONVINCED THE AUTHOR OF THE APPROPRIATENESS OF A QUALITATIVE APPROACH, TO A CONSIDERATION OF THE OUTCOMES GENERATED, THIS PAPER GUIDES THE READER THROUGH THE PROCESS OF QUALITATIVE DATA COLLECTION AND INDUCTIVE ANALYSIS EXPERIENCED BY THE AUTHOR. IN SO DOING, IT DEMONSTRATES THE VALUE OF USING SUCH AN APPROACH WHEN UNDERTAKING SMALL FIRMS RESEARCH." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="1999.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="QUALITATIVE MARKET RESEARCH AN INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.1108/13522759910269973" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.1108/13522759910269973" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
      <node id="CARLAND J, 1984, ACAD MANAGE REV" label="CARLAND J, 1984, ACAD MANAGE REV">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="DIFFERENTIATING ENTREPRENEURS FROM SMALL BUSINESS OWNERS: A CONCEPTUALIZATION" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="CARLAND J.W.; HOY F.; BOULTON W.R.; CARLAND J.A.C." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="JAMES W. CARLAND; FRANK HOY; WILLIAM R. BOULTON; JO ANN C. CARLAND" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="; ; ; " />
          <attvalue for="5" value="JAMES W. CARLAND, FRANK HOY, WILLIAM R. BOULTON, JO ANN C. CARLAND, DIFFERENTIATING ENTREPRENEURS FROM SMALL BUSINESS OWNERS: A CONCEPTUALIZATION, THE ACADEMY OF MANAGEMENT REVIEW, VOL. 9, NO. 2 (APR., 1984), PP. 354-359" />
          <attvalue for="6" value="1984.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="ACADEMY OF MANAGEMENT REVIEW" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="ACAD MANAGE REV" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.5465/AMR.1984.4277721" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.5465/amr.1984.4277721" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
