      <node id="SYMEONIDOU N, 2013" label="SYMEONIDOU N, 2013">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="RESOURCE ORCHESTRATION: THE EFFECTS OF RESOURCE INVESTMENT AND LEVERAGING STRATEGY ON PERFORMANCE" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="SYMEONIDOU N." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="NONI SYMEONIDOU" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="HTTPS://ORCID.ORG/0000-0002-5910-861X" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="THE PROCESS BY WHICH ENTREPRENEURS ACCUMULATE AND DEPLOY RESOURCES HAS IMPORTANT IMPLICATIONS FOR FIRM PERFORMANCE. ALTHOUGH THE RESOURCE BASED VIEW HIGHLIGHTS THE IMPORTANCE OF RESOURCES FOR THE CREATION OF COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE, IT HAS BEEN LESS ABLE TO ADDRESS HOW MANAGERS USE THESE RESOURCES TO CREATE VALUE OR HOW THESE ARE CONNECTED WITH THE STRATEGIES FIRMS PURSUE. BUILDING ON RESOURCE ORCHESTRATION RESEARCH, WE EXAMINE THE PERFORMANCE EFFECTS OF ALIGNING RESOURCE INVESTMENTS WITH DEPLOYING DECISIONS. USING A SAMPLE OF US START-UPS WE FIND THAT DEVIATING FROM RIVALS’ RESOURCE INVESTMENTS NEGATIVELY AFFECTS PERFORMANCE IN START-UPS, WHILE CONFORMING TO THE NORMS SET BY RIVALS POSITIVELY AFFECTS PERFORMANCE. HOWEVER, WE ALSO FIND THAT INVESTMENT DECISIONS ALONE ARE NOT SUFFICIENT TO PRODUCE THE BEST RESULTS IN START-UPS; INSTEAD, SUPERIOR PERFORMANCE IS PRODUCED WHEN RESOURCE INVESTMENTS AND LEVERAGING STRATEGY ARE PURPOSEFULLY SYNCHRONISED BY THE ENTREPRENEUR." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2013.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="ACADEMY OF MANAGEMENT PROCEEDINGS" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.5465/AMBPP.2013.14217ABSTRACT" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.5465/ambpp.2013.14217abstract" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
