      <node id="WEBSTER F, 1992, J MARKETING" label="WEBSTER F, 1992, J MARKETING">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="THE CHANGING ROLE OF MARKETING IN THE CORPORATION" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="WEBSTER F.E." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="FREDERICK E. WEBSTER" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="" />
          <attvalue for="5" value="NEW ORGANIZATION FORMS, INCLUDING STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIPS AND NETWORKS, ARE REPLACING SIMPLE MARKET-BASED TRANSACTIONS AND TRADITIONAL BUREAUCRATIC HIERARCHICAL ORGANIZATIONS. THE HISTORICAL MARKETING MANAGEMENT FUNCTION, BASED ON THE MICROECONOMIC MAXIMIZATION PARADIGM, MUST BE CRITICALLY EXAMINED FOR ITS RELEVANCE TO MARKETING THEORY AND PRACTICE IN THE 1990S. A NEW CONCEPTION OF MARKETING WILL FOCUS ON MANAGING STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIPS AND POSITIONING THE FIRM BETWEEN VENDORS AND CUSTOMERS IN THE VALUE CHAIN WITH THE AIM OF DELIVERING SUPERIOR VALUE TO CUSTOMERS. CUSTOMER RELATIONSHIPS WILL BE SEEN AS THE KEY STRATEGIC RESOURCE OF THE BUSINESS." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="1992.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="JOURNAL OF MARKETING" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="J MARKETING" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="10.1177/002224299205600402" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="10.1177/002224299205600402" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
