      <node id="GLIEM J, 2003" label="GLIEM J, 2003">
        <attvalues>
          <attvalue for="0" value="true" />
          <attvalue for="1" value="CALCULATING, INTERPRETING, AND REPORTING CRONBACH’S ALPHA RELIABILITY COEFFICIENT FOR LIKERT-TYPE SCALES" />
          <attvalue for="2" value="GLIEM J.A.; GLIEM R.R." />
          <attvalue for="3" value="JOSEPH A. GLIEM; ROSEMARY R. GLIEM" />
          <attvalue for="4" value="; " />
          <attvalue for="5" value="THE PURPOSE OF THIS PAPER IS TO SHOW WHY SINGLE-ITEM QUESTIONS PERTAINING TO A CONSTRUCT ARE&amp;#13;\NNOT RELIABLE AND SHOULD NOT BE USED IN DRAWING CONCLUSIONS. BY COMPARING THE RELIABILITY OF A SUMMATED, MULTI-ITEM SCALE VERSUS A SINGLE-ITEM QUESTION, THE AUTHORS SHOW HOW UNRELIABLE A SINGLE ITEM IS; AND THEREFORE IT IS NOT APPROPRIATE TO MAKE INFERENCES BASED UPON THE ANALYSIS OF SINGLE-ITEM QUESTIONS WHICH&amp;#13;\NARE USED IN MEASURING A CONSTRUCT." />
          <attvalue for="6" value="2003.0" />
          <attvalue for="7" value="IUSCHOLARWORKS (INDIANA UNIVERSITY)" />
          <attvalue for="8" value="" />
          <attvalue for="9" value="" />
          <attvalue for="10" value="" />
          <attvalue for="11" value="" />
        </attvalues>
      </node>
